                    <span>As an Executive Coach. Management Team Builder and Leadership Development Trainer I have found this book to be a finger, pointing at almost every executive I know. It clearly identifies how managers become their own worst enemy by virtue of the things they do (or don't do). In coaching executives I recommend this book in conjunction with Peter F. Drucker's "The Effective Executive" which defined the same principles 35 year beforehand and which was reissued in 2000.</span>
                  
              
